This paper proposes a novel authentication protocol for servers, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The protocol involves the use of cryptographic hashes generated through chaotic systems, which is a topic of interest in network security (cs.NI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the usability and design of the protocol, which falls under the categories of software engineering (cs.SE) and distributed systems (cs.DS).
